Dialogs.Dialog: Rinko
What's with all the couples today？ They are so close to each other. It's really embarrassing for me.
If we do the same, we won't be embarrassed, will we？
Ah, good idea！
Huh？
I'm kidding, unfortunately.
Rinko
A date in the park is a classic.
Too standard and boring？
That's not true.
Then that's fine.
A long-distance date is nice, but I also like to just walk around together without purpose.
Rinko
It's nice to have a date in the park, holding hands, even if you are both ojii-chan and obaa-chan.
Oh, those two？ I see them all the time.
We're neighbors, you know, and they're always close.
Then, why don't we try to follow their example？
I didn't mean it that way, but in the name of that couple, I'll allow it.
Rinko
After all, when you are a child, you often play hide-and-seek in the precincts of shrines.
Maybe so. I bet you were really active playing hide-and-seek, ▲小早川＊▲.
I was good at hiding. Even now, I'm confident that the amateurs will never find me.
Are you an expert in hide-and-seek？
Rinko is the one. She still hides from the sensei a lot, so she's honing her skills.
(Even if you're proud of yourself for that...)
Since we're here, let's pay a visit...
Rinko
...hey. What did you ask for？
That I might be with you forever, ▲小早川＊▲.
I don't know where I've heard such a thing before.
There is no need to be eccentric in this kind of thing. Simple is best. You like that too, right, ▲小早川＊▲？
...hehe, that's such a surprisingly decent reply. Yeah, I don't dislike it.
How about a matching good luck charm or something？
Rinko
I don't mind... but there are so many kinds. Prayers for traffic safety, family safety, safe delivery... I've had enough of love fulfillment.
If that's the case, then I guess, health and all that？
Hmm, doesn't sound like a high school student thing.
If there's one thing that's typical of high school students, it's academics.
Hmm, not very Rinko-esque.
(Indeed...)
You've been quiet for a while now. Wasn't that funny？
Rinko
...nah. I didn't know some movies could be this funny.
Heh, you liked it so much.
I often have trouble concentrating on a movie until the end, but that wasn't the case with this one.
That's unusually high praise. Even though it's dry.
Well yeah, so I'm sure the film will be a hit.
Rinko
Now that could have been rather interesting.
It's the hottest piece of the season.
I think the story lacks depth, but it's a good choice for a date movie, right？
Haha, as usual.
When watching in a theater, it's not only about the artistry, but also about TPO.
Rinko
I don't mean to tell you this, but the current movie was like giving back time.
Sorry...
I don't want you to apologize. I want to do something together.
Huh？
If I don't do that, I'm not going to feel good about it. If I kicked you a lot, it would make me feel a little better.
I see. Then I'll cooperate.
Rinko
I thought it's embarrassing to watch a romantic movie with my boyfriend...
How was it？
Good ...... once in a while.
Haha, I'm glad. Actually, I was getting a little embarrassed about it.
Rinko might be in a bit of a romantic mode right now. But that's just it, maybe.
Rinko
Hmm... that was fun！ Diving from the rooftop, that was exciting.
That wasn't CG.
And they don't use stunts, either. I feel like I'm rockin' it.
Then you liked it a lot.
Yeah. It's a good movie when you need to clear your mind.
How did you like it？ What did you think？
Rinko
No comment.
Eh, was it boring？
I said no comment, you know.
I mean, your face is kind of scrunched up.
If I'm distracted, I'm likely to laugh at the memory. Don't talk to me.
(Well, I guess that means it was good.)
Rinko
Is science fiction still a man's romance？
I know that's not the case for everyone, but are you saying that you didn't get it, ▲小早川＊▲？
I got the gist of it, but there's just too much unnecessary setup.
Yeah, that kind of thing, too.
I thought that was what romance was all about. Well, the story was interesting, so that's all that matters.
How was it, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
It was interesting, but not scary.
I wonder how that would work as a horror movie.
That's fine, as long as it's funny. I think Rinko would have enjoyed this even if it wasn't a horror movie.
You mean the story itself was good？
I'm talking about the visual techniques and direction. Horror movie lovers may have a different opinion.
Is an animated movie on a date too subtle？
Rinko
It's fine. Rinko enjoyed it rather well, though.
Surprising. I thought you were going to say it was childish.
I watch children's anime with my little brother, so maybe that's what I'm used to.
Heh, that's kind of counter -intuitive and mature, isn't it？
Hehe, you think？ A step backward, I guess.
Rinko
You know the way good throwers often curve their throws in the middle？
The ones that bend just short of the garter？
Yes. I'd like to do something like that.
I think the first step is to throw it straight at the target...
Okay, that's boring. I'll practice.
(I think you're going to have a string of gutters... Well, if it's fun, then so be it.)
Rinko
There are quite a lot of families.
Why don't you and your brother try it, ▲小早川＊▲？
I think it's still too difficult. When they are a little older, it would be nice to do it with the whole family.
Mm-hmm.
What, you look like an old meddling geezer again, you know？
Haha, well, that's about it.
Rinko
Ah, geez, I can't increase my score.
Not a bad score if you were a girl.
What if it was a girl？ Sexual harassment.
Eh, for this one？
I'm mad, I'm definitely going to surpass you...
(You've stirred up a weird sense of struggle...)
Rinko
Mmm, that was great！
It was worth coming.
Well, there were still some rough edges, but I think I have a good one.
Haha, if you say that, then means it was pretty good, ▲小早川＊▲？
We have to tell the word now, "I've had my eye on you for a while".
A live show is good. You think so too, don't you, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
I don't disagree with you there, but I'd like to see a few more surprises.
Surprise？
Yes. If I may say so, I would like to see something that can only be done live.
Sounds difficult.
You can't go for it, it's all luck.
(It's going to be difficult to completely satisfy you, ▲小早川＊▲.)
Rinko
...hah. After watching it with you, I'm sorry, but it wasn't good.
I guess so...
You're doing it without a hitch, but I feel like I'm getting used to it...
That's as tough as it gets.
If the viewer compromises, the culture is finished.
How was it？
Rinko
Crude, cheap music that has sold its soul to commercialism.
Huh？
I was wondering if you were expecting that kind of answer.
I thought it was pretty good, so that's indeed...
I know, I'm kidding. Rinko thought it was nice, too.
Rinko
Tori's band！ That was so good.
I thought so, too. You liked their show too, ▲小早川＊▲？
It's like "going my way". I like the way they don't care what's going on around them.
It was plain to look at, but the sound was most impressive.
It's thick and throbbing and it hits deep in the chest... That's real rock！
Rinko
Hey. Do you know what good jazz is？
When you ask me that way... I just think it's nice.
Rinko is like that. I wish I could explain it.
If it makes you feel good to listen to it, isn't that all that matters？
Maybe so, but... Rinko wants to know better.
Rinko
...hip-hop, huh？ Rinko doesn't know what young kids like these days.
Young kids these days, huh... aren't you one too, ▲小早川＊▲？
Because the spirit of Rinko's is in London in the 70's.
That's too wide open... then I guess today's is a bust.
...I might have actually been able to hear it. Surprising even to myself, I wonder why.
Rinko
You like this kind of thing, too.
Well... yes, I guess.
Hmm... Rinko liked it a lot, though.
You also have a cute voice, so isn't it nice, ▲小早川＊▲？
I don't mind the praise, but... it's not that simple a world, I'm sure.
Rinko
You know... doesn't it make you sleepy when you're listening to people in the dark？
Yeah, I can understand that.
I had a close call earlier, too.
The story was interesting, so I feel like that's what kept me connected. I went back and forth between sleep and reality.
That sounds kinda pleasant.
Did you watch these things when you were little？
Rinko
No, not really. I'm sure I won't be able to concentrate until the end.
Well... how was it now？
Yes, it was pretty interesting. Sometimes it was too surrealistic and unintelligible.
I see. I didn't thought you could understand that kind of thing, ▲小早川＊▲.
What do you mean？ You think Rinko's is surreal？
Rinko
Hehe. Actually, I was looking forward to karaoke today.
Oh, you're looking more determined than ever.
It's no wonder. I heard that the song I've been requesting was on the list.
I see. So today is the first day the song is sung.
Would you like a drink ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Better yet, I've got to put in a song soon. We are wasting time.
Just about time to choose a drink...
Okay, you go first. I've included a song for you. Good luck！
Eh？ Ah, geez, I get it.
Yeah！
Rinko
Okay, now I guess this is the next one... yeah, this one.
Huh？ This song is from...
Duet Song. Special service by Rinko's today.
Haha... that makes me shy.
If you are embarrassed, it makes me embarrassed too. Shyness is forbidden.
Rinko
Oh... no looking at the gondola over there.
Eh, what？ ...Oh, they're kissing.
Don't put those things into words.
Don't you worry about people looking at you？
Why ask Rinko, of course she's curious about it...
Oh, sorry. I stepped on your foot, didn't I？
Rinko
I don't mind. It's a small place on a Ferris wheel... hehe.
Hmm？ Did I say something funny？
Nah. Inside the Ferris Wheel... it's kind of nice to have our feet touching each other like this, isn't it？
Yes, it is...
I heard that the haunted house here has undergone a minor change and is twice as scary...
Rinko
There's a limit to what people can make.
That said, you should be a little more surprised.
No matter who or what stands in front of Rinko, be it a ghost or whatever... hiya！
(It's not easy being a ghost either...)
This one was pretty scary. ▲小早川＊▲...
Rinko
That's a foul. You're not scaring them, you're just startling them.
Well, yeah. Who wouldn't be surprised if someone jumped out at you all of a sudden.
It's a wicked idea. Rinko thinks we should redo the staging from the ground up.
(It must be pretty frustrating to be scared...)
...it's done. Now that was a hard one...
Rinko
Don't look so bitter. We're going to ride again.
What！？ ...are you still riding？
No wimping out！ Come on, let's get in line again.
Ugh...
Isn't this the kind of thing where a girl hugs her boyfriend and says, "Oh my god, I'm scared！"？
Rinko
Hmm... that's the kind of thing you want to do.
Well, in general？
Well, shall I give you a hug as a service？
Really！？
Oh, sorry. It wasn't a service day today. Maybe some other time.
(What's a service day？)
Rinko
...ah, geez, there are so many people, I can't see the parade.
Do you want me to carry you on my shoulders？
I'm not a child.
Then let's go to the steps over there.
...hey, can you see it here？
...yeah, it's pretty... hehe, this was worth watching.
Are you sleepy, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Hmm, just a little bit.
That's unusual. Shall we go home now？
That's fine. We came all the way here to see the parade, it'd be a waste of time.
Yes, but if you get sleepy, I'll lend you my shoulder.
...yeah, thanks.
▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
...hmm？
I've called you many times, and you were totally lost in it.
...well, Rinko is a girl too.
Haha, you're so honest.
Well, at least at a time like this... Forget the current Rinko's later.
Rinko
Oh, there's a beautiful lady waving at you！
Eh！？
...I wonder why you fall for such a simple thing.
It's not that, it's more like... conditional reflex.
Nope, nope, excuses are not good enough.
(What was I supposed to do...)
*Phew*... a little break.
Rinko
I haven't played enough. I've only been on the water slides five times！
Five times, I think...
Geez... I can't help it, you're an old man.
Good grief.
After a short break, I'll ride at least five more times, okay？
(...good grief.)
Rinko
I think you've been glancing at Rinko for a while now... what is it？
It's nothing out of the ordinary, there's nothing that says I shouldn't look at you.
You're eyes are suspicious.
I was born this way！
I see. You were born a pervert...
(That's an accusation...)
Rinko
Even though you know it's a video, it feels magical, like you're surrounded by stars.
...yeah, that's true.
I feel like I can forget about all these little things and be honest.
I see, then...
...then, what？ I feel some kind of deviousness, so I'm not going to be honest with you.
Rinko
The starry sky all around us... is still beautiful.
In reality, the city lights are so strong that it's rare to see so many stars.
Someday, somewhere far away, just the two of us, I'd like to see the stars... like this.
Is it important to be just us？
Don't react to that part. But that's the point. You know what I mean.
Rinko
You know, all the couples around us... they are all glued together.
Because of this atmosphere.
...that's not the point.
Well, let's get going.
That's not what I meant... geez, pay attention.
(That's hard...)
Rinko
With so many plants, it will be hard to take care of them.
They will all have diverse optimal conditions.
Come to think of it, Tama at Rinko's house is not doing well.
The cactus？
Yes. I'm sure someone from the staff here would be happy to discuss this with me.
Hmm, maybe.
Rinko
Plants sometimes have scientific names that are completely different from their commonly used Japanese names.
For example...？
This is Camellia, but it says... er, Camellia Japonica.
Heh, I'll call it that from now on then. Camellia Japonica！
No, it's so annoying. Do your best on your own.
Rinko
Ugh, it's so gloomy...
That's because it's tailored to the plant.
I wonder if there isn't a more comfortable place for humans to spend their time.
I don't know... it's a botanical garden.
You need to think more about the people who appreciate the plants. This facility cannot exist only for the plants on the side of the viewers.
(That's absurd...)
Rinko
Sometimes, you know, it's nice to come to an event like this. It was a lot of fun.
I see. That's good. It was worth coming.
I'm tired, but it's not a bad kind of tired.
Like you're addicted to it？
It's kind of light to say it, but... well, yeah, I feel like I'm hooked. I might even come back.
How was today's event？
Rinko
Hmm... not good nor bad, normal.
Normal, huh...
Maybe next time it will be better if the organizers know exactly what they need to improve.
Improvements, for example？
Let's leave aside the details of the event, such as... queuing, handling the entry, broadcasting during the event, and other little things like that. That's important, isn't it？
(You're surprisingly detail-oriented...)
Maybe you are in a bad mood ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
I can't believe that the attendant didn't direct me when it was that crowded.
Yeah... sure was a terrible operation.
This is a problem before the event. You can't have fun with this.
By the way, the event's content...
Oh, that one was the worst.
Rinko
I wonder why classical music attracts so much sleep.
Is it somehow the... rhythm that makes you sleepy？
But Rinko isn't breathing in his sleep like his neighbor, though, is she？
Yes. So there was only one person next to me.
...sorry.
...haha.
Rinko
...what.
At first you said that idol shows were boring... but then you liked them enough to buy their merchandise.
That's okay, I was really impressed.
I didn't say it was bad.
If so, that's fine. Idols are like wrestling, there are many fake ones, but the real ones are amazing.
(Oh, that's some hot stuff you're talking about...)
Rinko
I'm not sure if a musical is a concert or a play.
How was today？
...yeah, I still didn't understand it.
I see...
Don't be discouraged. It wasn't boring. It was rather fun, you know？
Really？ Then that's fine.
If we get too focused on formality, we will lose sight of the essence of what we are doing. The important thing is whether you enjoy it or not.
Rinko
I knew a live battle would be exciting.
I know, right～.
It's not like a game, but you can really feel the excitement, the breathing？ You can even feel it... Hiya！
...Ouch... You're stronger than usual.
Oh, sorry. I got excited. It might have been a medium kick.
(If it had been a big kick...)
Rinko
...so, the last inning. That's what you call a goodbye win？
You know most of the rules of baseball, don't you？
Well, sort of. The cheering was more interesting than that, though.
Haha, well, that's one way to have fun.
Especially the backflipping mascot！ It's creepy-cute♪
(Well yeah, it really was creepy-cute...)
Rinko
Rinko... is not good with crowds...
Everyone is so desperate, we can't compete with them.
Yes, it's not something you come here to see things. It's okay though, I had a good time.
Would it be more fun if we kept coming back？
Maybe so, but not that much... I'm too busy being a multi-talented Rinko.
Rinko
I heard that this Bay Bridge was featured in a magazine as a good dating spot.
A hidden spot... huh？ I think it's pretty major.
Hey, I bet the person in charge of that article was embarrassed. Poor guy.
Do you even worry about that？
I was saddened to think that someone would say, "I heard he didn't even know about the Bay Bridge".
Rinko
The view here is beautiful, it's like a picture postcard.
Um... "You're prettier than any landscape".
Yes, yes, that kind of thing doesn't suit you. Was it last week's drama？
Haha, you caught me. I just wanted to say these lines.
Rinko, you know, she'd be happy just to hear your true feelings, not such borrowed lines.
You know, when you do this, it feels kind of romantic, doesn't it？
Rinko
You think？ Rinko imagined a scene where a giant monster destroys the Bay Bridge.
You know... we're lovers, and we're a little more...
So, do you want to try something loverly？ Leaning on each other's shoulders or crossing each other's arms. You'd be embarrassed anyway.
That's a mutual benefit.
Hehe, who knows.
Rinko
If you see your girlfriend in a swimsuit, do you fall in love with her all over again？
Who knows... maybe.
Don't stare. You're not making me fall in love with you again, you're just a pervert old geezer.
I don't mean that. It's not like I can't see you anytime... I have to keep an eye on my girlfriend who is different from the norm.
I see... yes, but don't think it's less perverted by saying some pretty words.
(Ugh, maybe...)
Rinko
I always wonder. How do I get a nice body？
Well... you don't have to worry about that. I like you as you are, ▲小早川＊▲.
I'm glad you said that. I don't feel like I can imitate that kind of thing.
Yeah.
I have to give thanks for my lolicon boyfriend.
No, I'm not！
Rinko
Geez, you're my boyfriend, you better watch Rinko！
What's wrong？
Because you are dawdling, I was approached by a pick-up guy.
What！？ Sorry, are you okay？ Where is that guy...
Maybe he's in the hospital by now. And I did it with a kick.
That's why I said it's dangerous...
Isn't it cold in the water ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Not at all. It's just a little cold, it feels so nice.
Good grief... you are childish sometimes.
What did you say, old man？
Nope, nothing.
You know, standing barefoot on the beach feels good when the waves recede, so why don't you try it？
Yes, yes, I'll go with you.
Rinko
...hehe.
What's up, what did you find？
It's not that. When you are alone in a quiet place like this, don't you think that you and Rinko might be the only ones in the world？
Yes, I can understand that. What if we really are the only two people in the world？
But that's okay, isn't it？ I don't want to be alone, but together, maybe.
Rinko
...It's cold. You and Rinko must be idiots to be at the beach at this time of the year.
I thought the air was clear and pleasant.
Rinko prefers warm air to clear air.
Yes, yes.
Or better yet, a warm boyfriend... You know.
...yeah.
Rinko
I wonder what this guy is thinking.
Hmm, maybe rambling, just dawdling, and so on.
Rambling, dawdling... for short？
Ramda.
I don't have a cushion to take away, so... can I kick you as punishment？
Not good！
What's the matter, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Rinko is just buying a fight that was sold to her. He was the one who glared at me first.
A staring contest with a sunfish. Will you win or lose？
I can't read their expressions... and even then, I get the feeling they can see right through us. It's a nasty enemy.
(When did they become the enemy...)
Rinko
You know, can't we keep penguins？
It's going to be a challenge to recreate this environment at home. Do you want to keep them？
No way, I was just saying.
Right... I wonder if penguins take walks or something.
With a collar and leash？ It's kind of surreal.
Rinko
Penguins, you know, are charming creatures.
I think it's when it walks like a duck.
By nature, this is a win-win situation.
Haha, maybe you like them as much as you like cats？
That's not true. Cats are a little bit not that kind of thing, and they're in the Hall of Fame.
(As I thought.)
Wow... awesome！ A school of sardines is so powerful.
Rinko
The only time you should be loud and excited is when you are in elementary school. It's embarrassing for an old person.
Haha, sorry！
Ah！ Look, look. A manta ray is swimming！
Little children, remember...
Shut up, it's okay, it's a manta ray.
(I have no idea what's so great about it！)
Rinko
I wonder who invented the underwater tunnel.
They turned the tank into a tunnel, so it's a novelty.
They must have used the tunnel as an aquarium.
Eh... which one？
It doesn't matter either way. I'm talking about using the tunnel as an aquarium.
Rinko
When you come to an aquarium, you can't miss the dolphin show.
It's the centerpiece of the aquarium.
There are places where you can swim with dolphins, I wonder if they do it here.
Never heard of it...
What should I do, become a shareholder here？
(Are you dreamy or realistic？)
If you go too far, you'll get covered with water, ▲小早川＊▲.
Rinko
A little bit of water is the way to enjoy the dolphin show.
Okay, I'll try it too！
Whoa！？
Ah, what are you doing？
When did you run away, ▲小早川＊▲.
Hehe, it's Rinko's crisis avoidance skills honed in the gaming world.
(For real...)
Rinko
This park, you know, is popular with couples.
Yeah, I hear it increases even more late at night for some reason.
I see...
It's not a story that high school students can relate to.
Hmm, you look different and fresh.
I'm telling you, I'm always fresh.
Rinko
I think Rinko might rather like the view of the ocean from this park.
I see. Sometimes you can even see passenger ships leaving the harbor.
Now if only it would make the atmosphere a little less buoyant.
You think？ It's pretty quiet.
Not the sound, but the atmosphere. It's like a date spot.
(I guess we're dating too...)
Rinko
There is a little wind today.
Yes... This one looks like a park by the sea, though.
Yes, it's not too clammy. It's quite comfortable.
When it comes to the ocean and wind, all that is left is...
Like lightning？ You know, for the accent.
(It's going to be uncomfortable all at once...)
Rinko
When you look down like this, don't you feel like you're getting sucked in？
Oh, maybe you're afraid of high places？
For this... I'm just imaginative. That's why the appearance of being sucked in is realistic...
It's true that you have a lot of imagination, but it's more like... delusional power？
(It's a false accusation... maybe.)
Rinko
You know, this place has a lot of couples, but the souvenirs are weak.
Sky Tower crackers and Sky Tower midgets... like that.
They should make a Sky Tower transforming robot or something, my little brother would be happy.
That would be great for the kids...
Let's really make the tower transformable and make it an attraction！ What do you think？
Haha, that sounds really interesting.
Rinko
When you are in a building like this, don't you wonder how you would escape in an emergency？
I don't, but I think... that's too cautious or too negative.
Maybe, but I think it's a pretty fun fantasy.
Fantasy？ You're talking about an escape device, right？
Sliding down a slider to escape, or being ejected by a small one-person rocket, that sort of thing.
(Is this another influence from the robot anime you watch with your little brother？)
Rinko
I'm going to go try it on, just give me a minute. Please let me know what you think.
Yeah, leave it to me.
Hmm, what's up？
...I feel like it's a bit unforgivable right now, like how it's a standard couple's conversation...
It doesn't matter if it's a classic, as long as it's fun.
Rinko
The world is supposed to have become convenient, but how can you have trouble finding clothes just because your body size is a little off the average？
Is that how it is？ Yes, it seems to be more difficult for girls.
It's true, girls' bodies are more... what can I say, there's a lot of variety.
Variety？ What do you mean？
It's... look, out and back in, that sort of thing！
(Let's not poke around any more...)
Rinko
I forget how time flies when I'm here.
I don't know if I like this kind of thing that much.
I just don't like any unnecessary jingling, I like it to be casual.
Hehe... like this necklace for example.
Yes, those... prices don't seem to be casual.
Rinko
It's often said that an engagement ring is three months' salary. I wonder who decided that.
Something about it being the manufacturer's catchphrase, or something.
Hmm. So you don't have any solid evidence.
I guess so. But for three months！ That sounds inspired, doesn't it？
I don't mind if it's a few months' worth, but if you emphasize the price too much, I'm a little put off.
(That's how it is...)
Are you into makeup too, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
That's because I'm a girl. At the moment, I'm mostly just interested.
Well, you don't need it.
What are you talking about？ Oh, I remember when you said your girlfriend is the type who wants to do things her own way.
It's not like that. It's just that you're so beautiful to begin with...
Hmm... hehe, just make sure you say it right to the end.
There are so many types, it would be hard to just choose one.
Rinko
